<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="_1EUJotnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" name="use-case_view,6.820983346069146E-305" guid="_1EUJotnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA" changeDate="2005-06-29T10:48:49.769-0700" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_use-case_view__introduction_to&quot; name=&quot;XE_use-case_view__introduction_to&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To provide a basis for planning the technical contents of iterations, an &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/software_architecture_4269A354.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;3.066252221588648E-305&quot;>architectural view&lt;/a> called the &lt;b>use-case view&lt;/b> is used in the following: &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/disciplines/rup_requirements_discipline_8EEB5209.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_ydt60dnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA&quot;>Requirements&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;discipline. There is only one use-case view of the system, which&#xD;
    illustrates the use cases and scenarios that encompass architecturally significant behavior, classes, or technical&#xD;
    risks. The use-case view is refined and considered initially in each iteration.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p class=&quot;picturelarge&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;map id=&quot;FPMap0&quot; name=&quot;FPMap0&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;area shape=&quot;rect&quot; alt=&quot;Use Cases&quot; coords=&quot;408,177,484,238&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_A5D30E62.html&quot; guid=&quot;{B1526BC5-E346-42CB-A08A-3C0D7F382407}&quot; />&#xD;
        &lt;area shape=&quot;rect&quot; alt=&quot;Actors&quot; coords=&quot;344,172,397,234&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_actor_1F9CE9.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{0EEBBA43-F5C6-4594-9F06-65D99F7556DF}&quot; />&#xD;
        &lt;area shape=&quot;rect&quot; alt=&quot;Use-Case Packages&quot; coords=&quot;354,101,477,164&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_package_A96DDE65.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{102E424E-98DE-4F54-B1A0-8F8FD54D6BEE}&quot; />&#xD;
        &lt;area shape=&quot;rect&quot; alt=&quot;Top-Level Package&quot; coords=&quot;360,31,476,85&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_design_package_8376BC8E.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{80CC5437-F481-487B-A69B-957D9D236D8D}&quot; />&#xD;
        &lt;area shape=&quot;rect&quot; alt=&quot;The Use-Case Model&quot; coords=&quot;328,0,476,23&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_model_EF15E534.html&quot; guid=&quot;{9C66F2EC-EDEB-4369-9AFB-04B9E7CBCB8E}&quot; />&#xD;
    &lt;/map>&lt;img height=&quot;241&quot; alt=&quot;Diagram described in accompanying text.&quot; src=&quot;resources/co_ucv1.gif&quot; width=&quot;505&quot;&#xD;
    usemap=&quot;#fpmap0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p class=&quot;picturetext&quot;>&#xD;
    The use-case view shows an architecturally significant subset of the use-case model, a subset of the use cases and&#xD;
    actors.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The analysis, design, and implementation activities subsequent to requirements are centered on the notion of an &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/software_architecture_4269A354.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;3.066252221588648E-305&quot;>&lt;b>architecture&lt;/b>&lt;/a>. The production and validation of that architecture is the main&#xD;
    focus of the early iterations, especially during the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/customcategories/elaboration_6A203A50.html&quot; guid=&quot;_-kFhcCVuEdqSZ9OimJ-AzA&quot;>Elaboration&lt;/a> phase.&#xD;
    Architecture is represented by a number of different &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/software_architecture_4269A354.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;3.066252221588648E-305&quot;>architectural views&lt;/a>, which in their essence are extracts illustrating the&#xD;
    &quot;architecturally significant&quot; elements of the models.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There are four additional views: the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/logical_view_C135365E.html&quot; guid=&quot;6.901347907565747E-305&quot;>Logical View&lt;/a>, &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/process_view_E3DD0B09.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;6.45284088262517E-306&quot;>Process View&lt;/a>, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/deployment_view_64CB74A6.html&quot; guid=&quot;2.8416696002928195E-305&quot;>Deployment&#xD;
    View&lt;/a>, and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/concepts/implementation_view_E373E3B6.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;4.693519701160983E-305&quot;>Implementation View&lt;/a>. These views are handled in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/disciplines/rup_analysis_design_discipline_29760231.html&quot; guid=&quot;_ydt62NnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA&quot;>Analysis&#xD;
    &amp;amp; Design&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/disciplines/rup_implementation_discipline_263E22DB.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_yd3ExNnmEdmO6L4XMImrsA&quot;>Implementation&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;disciplines.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The architectural views are documented in a &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_software_architecture_document_C367485C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{6F49641A-ED10-47B5-9E5D-3F90A6BF3006}&quot;>Software Architecture Document&lt;/a>. You may add different views, such as&#xD;
    a security view, to convey other specific aspects of the software architecture.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    So, in essence, architectural views can be seen as abstractions or simplifications of the models built, in which you&#xD;
    make important characteristics more visible by leaving the details aside. The architecture is an important means for&#xD;
    increasing the quality of any model built during system development.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
